Use consistent indentation and naming standards to keep your C++ code nice and structured. Use camelCase or snake case for variable and function names, and indent consistently. This simplifies coding. Use meaningful variable, function, and code names. This would improve readability. Functions and classes: Use functions and classes to arrange your C++ code. Modularizing your code makes it simpler to maintain and comprehend. Functions and classes organize and encapsulate data and functionality. This improves code readability and maintainability. Commenting each function, class, and variable's purpose can help others comprehend the code. 